value: Provenance: Thomas Whitehurst (armorial bkpl.). Price code on front e.p.

Second ed. of v. 1-8, ending with the reign of Charles I, originally published 1724-1725; posthumous 1st ed. of v. 9-10, ending with the accession of William III.
"Lettre a Monsieur *** contenant quelques particularitez de la vie de Mr. de Rapin Thoyras": v. 1, p. 1-16 following dedication. Written by Rapin's elder brother Charles de Rapin Puginier (see DNB).
"Dissertation sur les Whigs et les Torys": v. 10, p. [196]-253 (half title; caption title, p. [201]: Dissertation sur l'origine du gouvernement d'Angleterre, et sur la naissance, les progrès, les vûës, les forces, les intérêts, & les caractéres des deux partis des Whigs & des Torys).
With half titles to each volume. Engraved title vignettes.
Three further v. were published later.
Old classmark: 540.
Binding: sprinkled calf; spine & board edges g.t., raised bands, g. lettering on spine labels; a.e. red.
Histoire d'Angleterre / par Mr. de Rapin Thoyras ...
10 v ([9] leaves of plates, [17] folded leaves of plates) : ports, map, tables ; 26cm (4to).
